    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2743186823" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2743186823" />
    <a title="Joan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7788548-joan"><img alt="Joan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1329450459p2/7788548.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2743186823?book_show_action=true">Mar 14, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Joan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Joan" href="/user/show/7788548-joan">Joan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2743186823" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14291737223102783767">I was hooked after reading the rich metaphor in the first sentence, which I re-read and savored several times. I loved the beautifully drawn main character, Angel. Her humanity, wit, wisdom and introspective musings bring her to life on every page. The story is set in post-genocide Rwanda, where Angel is a clever and entrepreneurial baker of cakes. We are given a vivid and endearing picture of a small tight knit community, and the interactions of a colorful cast of characters that includes ex-pa</span>
  <span id="freeText14291737223102783767" style="display:none">I was hooked after reading the rich metaphor in the first sentence, which I re-read and savored several times. I loved the beautifully drawn main character, Angel. Her humanity, wit, wisdom and introspective musings bring her to life on every page. The story is set in post-genocide Rwanda, where Angel is a clever and entrepreneurial baker of cakes. We are given a vivid and endearing picture of a small tight knit community, and the interactions of a colorful cast of characters that includes ex-pats who have various roles in the Rwanda’s reconstruction and locals who have endured tragic losses as a result of the genocide and the AIDS epidemic. Author, Gaile Parkin, in an interview included @ the end of the book, stated that, following her 2 years in Kigali, she was striving to give the reader a gentle story that would show the humor, joy and light the people bring to their lives, without trivializing the dark horrors they have endured. I think she has achieved this goal. I could not put the book down, and I came away with a better understanding of Rwanda, and a deeper sense of the goodness in people, even in the aftermath of unimaginable evil. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14291737223102783767" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

